name: Biquadratefree numbers (A046100) that are not squarefree (A005117).
comment: Subsequence of A252849 and first differs from it at n = 22: A252849(22) = 64 = 2^6 is not a term of this sequence.
Subsequence of A375229 and differs from it by not having the terms 1, 256, 512, 768, 1024, ... .
Numbers whose prime factorization has least one exponent that equals 2 or 3 and no higher exponent.
The asymptotic density of this sequence is 1/zeta(4) - 1/zeta(2) = A215267 - A059956 = 0.3160113... .
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ Pi^4 * n^2 / (12*(15 - Pi^2)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Apr 11 2025
program: (PARI) isok(k) = if(k == 1, 0, my(emax = vecmax(factor(k)[, 2])); emax > 1 & emax < 4);
def f(x): return int(n+x+sum(mobius(k)*(x//k**2-x//k**4) for k in range(1, integer_nthroot(x,4)[0]+1))+sum(mobius(k)*(x//k**2) for k in range(integer_nthroot(x,4)[0]+1,isqrt(x)+1)))
xref: Disjoint union of A067259 and A375072.

name: The number of non-unitary prime divisors of the n-th biquadratefree number that is not squarefree.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
mathematica: f[k_] := If[k == 1, Nothing, Module[{e = FactorInteger[k][[;; , 2]]}, If[2 <= Max[e] <= 3, Count[e, _?(# > 1 &)], Nothing]]]; Array[f, 1000]
program: (PARI) list(lim) = {my(e, emax); for(k = 2, lim, e = factor(k)[, 2]; emax = vecmax(e); if(emax > 1 && emax < 4, print1(#select(x -> x > 1, e), ", ")));}
